{"t": 1781063580.425511, "argv": ["SubagentStop"], "payload": {"session_id": "9870520e-ae2e-495e-a066-17be05c7e86e", "transcript_path": "/Users/dev/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-cue-audit-proj/9870520e-ae2e-495e-a066-17be05c7e86e.jsonl", "cwd": "/private/tmp/cue-audit-proj", "permission_mode": "default", "agent_id": "a227da54638117df4", "agent_type": "Explore", "hook_event_name": "SubagentStop", "stop_hook_active": false, "agent_transcript_path": "/Users/dev/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-cue-audit-proj/9870520e-ae2e-495e-a066-17be05c7e86e/subagents/agent-a227da54638117df4.jsonl", "last_assistant_message": "## Summary\n\nThe `/private/tmp/cue-audit-proj` directory contains an auditing setup for Claude Code:\n\n**Files:**\n- **capture-hook.py** - A Python script that captures Claude Code hook events and writes them to `/tmp/cue-hook-capture.jsonl` with timestamps, command-line arguments, and JSON payloads\n- **testfile** - An empty test file\n- **.claude/settings.json** - Configuration file that registers the capture-hook.py script across 15 different Claude Code lifecycle hooks\n\n**What this does:**\nThe project sets up comprehensive event capture across virtually all Claude Code lifecycle events:\n- Session management (Start, End)\n- User interactions (UserPromptSubmit)\n- Tool usage (PreToolUse, PostToolUse, PostToolUseFailure)\n- System events (Notification, PermissionRequest, Stop, StopFailure)\n- Subagent lifecycle (SubagentStart, SubagentStop)\n- Memory management (PreCompact, PostCompact)\n- Task completion (TaskCompleted)\n\nThis appears to be an audit/monitoring setup that logs all Claude Code activity and events to a JSONL file for analysis or debugging purposes.", "background_tasks": [], "session_crons": []}}
